This paper focuses on age estimation from facial images and videos using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a fog computing architecture for efficient age estimation, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) and networking (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of the proposed system in city surveillance and population analysis, which could be relevant to the field of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
